[https://creators.vrchat.com/avatars/avatar-dynamics/contacts VRChat Contact Senders & Receivers] can have custom tags. The VRCSDK comes with a [https://creators.vrchat.com/common-components/contacts/built-in-contact-tags built-in list] of tags and this page is a community driven expansion of them. 
[[File:CollisionTags.png|none|thumb|Example usage of custom collision tags]]

==Naming Conventions==

* Use PascalCase
* Avoid spaces, use _ if needed
* Clarity is important but brevity is appreciated
* Avoid using abbreviations/acronyms unless they are widely accepted
* Avoid single letter tags

== Collision Tags ==
Broken down into general categories. Some of these will overlap with the [https://creators.vrchat.com/common-components/contacts/built-in-contact-tags built-in list.]<ref>[https://creators.vrchat.com/common-components/contacts/built-in-contact-tags Built-In Contact Tags]</ref>

You may have up to # Tags on each Contact so using all applicable tags is usually good. (EG: Consumable and ConsumableFood together)

